===Etymology===
:Slavic ''voda'', ''woda'', meaning [[water]], plus the diminutive suffix ''-ka''. Historical documentary research of V. Pokhlyobkin suggests the derivation via the usage "dilution (of [[distil]]late) with water", as used in expressions "vodka of bread wine" and similar; ''bread wine'' ([[хлебное вино]]) is an archaic Russian name for vodka.

===Noun===
